article.headline: Jackson State 81, Prairie View 71 (OT)
article.story: JACKSON, Miss. (AP) -- Kelly Ross had five of his 13 points in overtime to lead Jackson State to an 81-71 victory over Prairie View A&M on Monday night. Jackson State (11-14, 7-6 Southwestern Athletic Conference) forced overtime on Hilton Thompkins' 3-pointer with 8.4 seconds left. The Tigers then outscored Prairie View 15-5 in OT to win their second straight -- both without suspended freshman guard Charlie White. Dakari Willis had 17 points to lead Jackson State, which has won four of five. Thompkins and Ernest Hassell had 14 apiece and Catraiva Givens added 10 points for the Tigers. Oscar Thompson had 22 points to lead Prairie View (4-17, 4-8), which led by as many as 12 in the first half but has lost two straight and four of five. Dominique Sharpe added 14 points for the Panthers. White served the second of a three-game suspension issued by the SWAC for punching a Southern U. player Feb. 7. He isn't eligible to play again until Feb. 26 at Mississippi Valley State.
